Former Aviation Minister, Stella Adaeze Oduah has arrived at the Federal High Court sitting in Abuja to take her plea in the alleged N7.9 billion fraud charges brought against her by the Federal Government. Stella Oduah is to be arraigned before Justice Inyang Eden Ekwo, alongside two other women and four companies. Daily Independent gathered that among the companies is the construction giant, China Civil Engineering Corporation (CCECC). -Advertisement- In a similar vein, Dr Hassan Liman, SAN, the Federal Governmentâ€™s lawyer has also arrived in court. About five Senior Advocates of Nigeria are also in court to defend the Senator and her co-defendants. Other defendants are Gloria Odita, Nwosu Emmanuel Nnamdi, Chukwuma Irene Chinyere, Global Offshore, and Marine Limited, Tip Top Global Resources Limited, Crystal Television Limited, Sobora International Limited, and a foreign construction company. They are charged with conspiracy and money laundering, as well as maintaining anonymous bank accounts.